reviews.review_text: Love This Site Thanks for the Great Shows a gem with excellent sound!!

Red Red Red Hot Rooster This show is full of amazing energy from the boys.  Little Red Rooster is usually not a gem for me, but this version is insanely good and emotional.  All in all a very good show worth checking out. Brokedown = CHILLS!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Mexican Bobby This show has the only instance I know of Bobby speaking in faux Mexican accent (immediately before Estimated, he addresses the throngs to explain an equipment problem)

There is a lot of jamming in this show (by late 1980 standards).  The meltdown after He's Gone is particularly out-there.

Great board - after Aiko This is a wonderful show from a great run and after the initial loud audience goes into a superior quality board. This may be the Ripple used in Reckoning. The Let it grow is along with Seattle one of the hottest of the year. Check out the aborted beginning of an awesome Estimated never heard that before.... Hilarious.

Great show very definately worth a listen.

Shucks One of the few great sounding standout electric shows from the RCMH - however it is marred by the puzzling yet ubiquitous fact that Jerry's guitar is the quietest instrument  in the mix. This is such a common thing in 80s SBDs - what the hell happened with this?

My first show This was my first show.  My friend Phil and I chose this over "The Wall" on the Island (we were 16 and had little money) little did I know it would take me up and down the east coast for another 15 years and some 90+ shows. Floyd disbanded the next year, though our love for the dead would not fade away.

Awesome Show I was at this show and it still ranks as one the funnest shows i ever went to. Radio City was great place to see the dead. He's Gone is unbelieveable and the crowd was definately into what was going on.
